==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Idolater
<hw>I*dol"a*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>idol⟦acir⟧tre</ets>: cf. L. <ets>idololatres</ets>, Gr. <?/. See
<er>Idolatry</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A worshiper of idols; one who
pays divine honors to images, statues, or representations of anything
made by hands; one who worships as a deity that which is not God; a
pagan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An adorer; a great admirer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Jonson was an <qex>idolater</qex> of the ancients.</q>
<rj><qau>Bp. Hurd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idolatress</ent>⟦br⟧
